workflow.name: Generate marketing campaign ROI reports with Google Sheets, GPT-4o and Email
workflow.description:
This n8n workflow pulls campaign data from Google Sheets, summarizes it using OpenAI, and sends a performance recap via Outlook email.

---

### ‚úÖ Step 1: Connect Google Sheets

1. In n8n, go to **Credentials** ‚Üí click **New Credential**
2. Select **Google Sheets OAuth2 API**
3. Log in with your Google account and authorize
4. Use a spreadsheet with:
   - Column names in the first row  
   - Data in rows 2‚Äì100  
5. Example format: [üìÑ Sample Marketing Sheet](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1UDWt0-Z9fHqwnSNfU3vvhSoYCFG6EG3E-ZewJC_CLq4/edit?usp=sharing)

---

### ‚úÖ Step 2: Connect OpenAI

1. Go to [OpenAI API Keys](https://platform.openai.com/api-keys)
2. Make sure you have a payment method set under [Billing](https://platform.openai.com/settings/organization/billing/overview)
3. In n8n, create a new **OpenAI API** credential
4. Paste your API key and save

### ‚úÖ Step 1: Connect Google Sheets

1. In n8n, go to **Credentials** ‚Üí click **New Credential**
2. Select **Google Sheets OAuth2 API**
3. Log in with your Google account and authorize
4. Use a spreadsheet with:
   - Column names in the first row  
   - Data in rows 2‚Äì100  
5. Example format: [üìÑ Sample Marketing Sheet](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1UDWt0-Z9fHqwnSNfU3vvhSoYCFG6EG3E-ZewJC_CLq4/edit?usp=sharing)

parameters.content:
### 2. Prepare Your Google Sheet

#### Connect your Data in Google Sheets
- Data must be in a format similar to this: [Sample Marketing Data](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1UDWt0-Z9fHqwnSNfU3vvhSoYCFG6EG3E-ZewJC_CLq4/edit?gid=365710158#gid=365710158)
- First row contains column names
- Data in rows 2-100
- Log in with OAuth2 and choose your workbook and sheet
- Optional: Try connecting to Airtable, Notion or your Database
### AI Agent analyzes data and sends daily email

options.systemMessage:
You are a Marketing Performance Assistant.

Use the data access campaign data, including fields like: campaign name, cost, impressions, clicks, conversions, and revenue.



Your job is to write a clear and helpful summary of campaign performance for a marketing team.

Your response must be in **JSON format** with only one field:

- `"output"`: A string that contains:
  - A short paragraph explaining overall performance
  - 3‚Äì5 bullet points with key insights
  - Total spend, impressions, clicks, conversions, and revenue (as bullets)

Use natural, business-friendly language and make it sound like part of a weekly email report. Use emojis if helpful. Do not include raw data or tables.

**Example format:**

```json
{
  "output": "Overall, campaign performance was strong this week. Retargeting efforts delivered the highest return, while a few awareness campaigns underperformed in conversions.\n\n‚Ä¢ üìà 'Spring Retargeting' had the highest ROAS at 9.1\n‚Ä¢ üí∞ 'Loyalty Push' generated $12,000 revenue on $1,600 spend\n‚Ä¢ üìâ 'Awareness Boost - TikTok' had low conversions despite high spend\n‚Ä¢ üß† Meta Ads accounted for 70% of total conversions\n\nTotals:\n‚Ä¢ Total Spend: $12,480\n‚Ä¢ Impressions: 983,400\n‚Ä¢ Clicks: 23,980\n‚Ä¢ Conversions: 1,482\n‚Ä¢ Revenue: $48,000"
}

### 1. Set Up OpenAI Connection

#### Get API Key:
1. Go to [OpenAI Platform](https://platform.openai.com/api-keys)
1. Go to [OpenAI Billing](https://platform.openai.com/settings/organization/billing/overview)
2. Add funds to your billing account & copy your api key into the openAI credentials
